      <scopecontent id="aspace_6cfcdd656d734db497e165d736f49da1">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains approximately 250 items which relate chiefly to Nantucket, Massachusetts, and to the Gardner, Pinkham, Swain, and Coffin families who lived there. The bulk of the collection consists of receipts, bills, accounts, and other financial papers, deeds, papers pertaining to estates and to several ships. There is also a small amount of correspondence, and a short diary kept by Silas Gardner (1753-1826). Silas Gardner is the person best represented in the collection; his nephew Paul Pinkham, Jr. (1763-1807) is also prominent in the collection. The latter was a trader living in Nantucket, Londonderry (New Hampshire), and Cape Porpoise (Maine), and co-owner with Peter Gardner of the sloop <title render="italic">
               <part>Pomona</part>
            </title>.</p>
         <p>These papers were purchased for Yale University in 1953.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
